 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#212141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ugaliaan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Galiaan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://users.erols.com/gww6e/eq/g.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Demi-God</span><br>  Posts: 1092<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/23/02 8:33:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub114.ezboard.com/flegacyofsteel43089general.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2879.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HELP! Comp probs</span><hr size=1> sounds like your computer runs out of ram, should double check you have enough room on your HDD for the swapfile, EQ-SoL can use up to 1Gigabyte of ram, so to be on the safe side have enough room for your ram+swapfile is around 1.2Gigs  <p><a href=http://www.legacyofsteel.net/view_player.php?player_id=25>Galiaan</a><br>Officer and Manasponge<br><a href=http://www.legacyofsteel.com>Legacy of Steel</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ufaylinsongstrider.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Faylin Songstrider</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/23/02 12:05:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub114.ezboard.com/flegacyofsteel43089general.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2879.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: HELP! Comp probs</span><hr size=1> Also could be a heat issue.  Something like this used to happen to me until I realized I had a heat issue and added two casefans pointing right at my vid card and one at my CPU.<br>
<br>
What kind of system are you running?  AMD Athlons are known to run rather hot, and nVidia GeForce cards are also hotter than hell...my Athlon XP + GF3 had my internals running around 130 degrees ferenheit.  Also make sure any air intakes in your case are not sucking in hot air, i.e. right next to your monitor. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#212141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/unebulis01.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nebulis01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/23/02 4:39:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub114.ezboard.com/flegacyofsteel43089general.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2879.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> 130 Degrees</span><hr size=1> u have serious heat problems <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  even though thats well within specs<br>
<br>
My bro is running a Athlon XP 1900+ Stock Fan and a GF3 Stock Fan and he maintains a closed cased temp of under 110degrees, then again he has 12case fans? :O <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uaaealorn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aaealorn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/23/02 6:28:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub114.ezboard.com/flegacyofsteel43089general.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2879.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> tried tried tried</span><hr size=1> Well, i'm running a Diamond Stealth III 32 mb card...i've only got 256 mb ram, and a 555 mhz processor, but my friend runs sol with 128 and a 433 just as well as i do WITHOUT the shutdown program...but the heat issue i've tried to compensate for...i have no money get get extra fans...i'm quite broke, so i tried putting a portable fan on it but it will shut down...so any ideas on anythign else i could do for it? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#212141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/blegacyofsteel43089.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=xaen>Xaen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/23/02 7:22:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub114.ezboard.com/flegacyofsteel43089general.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2879.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> Does it only shut down while playing EQ, or anytime? <br>
<br>
The only time ive seen a system actually shut itself down is from overheating, and that was an abrupt power-off .. Not a &quot;nice&quot; shutdown like you would get by going to the start-menu. Other than that, maybe check out a free virus scanner and see whats up. I've seen a few amusing programs that people sometimes get running in the background that can do this.<br>
<br>
If you're positive that it's a heat issue, new fans are really really cheap. If you dont have any money, then pop the case open and see if you can maybe move some cards around for better airflow, or move what fans you DO have in there around to better locations. If it's cold in your house/apt because of winter, then try running the machine with the case off .. But if its warm, then dont, because that will make it worse.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uaaealorn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aaealorn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/23/02 7:51:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub114.ezboard.com/flegacyofsteel43089general.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2879.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> only eq</span><hr size=1> It only happens when i'm on EQ. I'm not certian of anything other than i could have hit 45 a month ago, on my monk if i could keep a DL group on my 43 monk. But thats hard when i randomly shut down. i don't think it's a RAM prob..cause i figure, ram overload would happen about the same time every time because i'm almost always in the same place, but it's a randomthing, some times i go a whole night without it happening, sometimes i'm on for 20 min and WHAM, it restarts on it's own. It isn't cold here..but i just put an AC unit in my room, and my hard disks are set to shut off ever 2 hours if my comp goes unused to keep it cooled off inside....i'm gonna start running my AC window unit for an hour ever 2 hours, keep my room coldand run it with the case off. any other advice would be greatly appreciated, and thanks for all the help already! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#212141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uplanetium.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Planetium</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.covad.net/~swing4daddy/eyes_066.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/26/02 2:17:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub114.ezboard.com/flegacyofsteel43089general.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2879.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.badassbuddy.com/images/buddies/badassbuddy_com-pimp.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: only eq</span><hr size=1> this may sound dumb, but is your power plug anywhere near you? i can't say how many times i've simply kicked the surge protector and accidentally shut it down... <p><BR><img src=http://www.w3rd.org/img/sigs/planetsig.jpg>
